This paper deals with video summarization, which is a problem in computer vision (CV). The proposed method uses machine learning (ML) to learn a mapping function, which falls under the category of ML (MM). The paper also discusses the use of visual diversity constraint, which is a common technique in generative models and falls under the category of deep learning (LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of collecting training data, which is a common issue in information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.AI.
